<paragraph id="F165564AE235FFCD72F6FF780635FE5B" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E235FFCD72F6FF780491FF1F" bold="true" box="[151,487,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Justification of the transfer:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="954B2BBBE235FFCD738EFF7807F7FF1F" author="Shear" box="[495,641,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" refString="Shear, W. A. (1978) Taxonomic notes on the armored spiders of the families Tetrablemmidae and Pacullidae. American Museum Novitates, 2650, 1 - 46." type="journal article" year="1978">Shear (1978)</bibRefCitation>
described this species as 
<taxonomicName id="36DA2DC9E235FFCD71C3FF7801E4FF1F" authorityName="Shear" authorityYear="1978" box="[930,1170,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Monoblemma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="browni">
<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E235FFCD71C3FF7801E4FF1F" box="[930,1170,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Monoblemma browni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of a single male from 
<collectingCountry id="89CD16DAE235FFCD7370FF5304ECFF7A" box="[273,410,188,213]" name="Madagascar" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="954B2BBBE235FFCD73C4FF53072FFF7B" author="Lehtinen" box="[421,601,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" refString="Lehtinen, P. T. (1981) Spiders of the Oriental-Australian region. III. Tetrablemmidae, with a world revision. Acta Zoologica Fennica, 162, 1 - 151." type="journal article" year="1981">Lehtinen (1981)</bibRefCitation>
transferred this species to 
<taxonomicName id="36DA2DC9E235FFCD71E5FF530698FF7A" authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1981" box="[900,1006,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Shearella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E235FFCD71E5FF530698FF7A" box="[900,1006,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Shearella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Judging from the original description and illustrations of the male (
<bibRefCitation id="954B2BBBE235FFCD73BDFF300729FF57" author="Shear" box="[476,607,223,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" refString="Shear, W. A. (1978) Taxonomic notes on the armored spiders of the families Tetrablemmidae and Pacullidae. American Museum Novitates, 2650, 1 - 46." type="journal article" year="1978">Shear 1978</bibRefCitation>
), this species better fits the diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName id="36DA2DC9E235FFCD76E8FF300055FF57" authorityName="Gertsch" authorityYear="1941" box="[1161,1315,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Monoblemma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E235FFCD76E8FF300055FF57" box="[1161,1315,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Monoblemma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than those of 
<taxonomicName id="36DA2DC9E235FFCD72DBFEEB0452FEB2" authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1981" box="[186,292,260,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Shearella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E235FFCD72DBFEEB0452FEB2" box="[186,292,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Shearella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: it has a less compact eye group which is not elevated on a conical tubercle in the male, male chelicerae with short curving apophysis, clypeus with a pair of setae, and palpal bulb piriform, with long unmodified embolus. The features mentioned by Lehtinen to distinguish this species from 
<taxonomicName id="36DA2DC9E235FFCD76D9FEA205B9FE27" authority="Gertsch, 1941" authorityName="Gertsch" authorityYear="1941" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Monoblemma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicum">
<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E235FFCD76D9FEA20042FECB" box="[1208,1332,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">M. unicum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="954B2BBBE235FFCD775FFEA305B9FE27" author="Gertsch" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" refString="Gertsch, W. J. (1941) Report on some arachnids from Barro Colorado Island, Canal Zone. American Museum Novitates, 1146, 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="1941">Gertsch, 1941</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are merely species-specific and are not sufficient enough to alter its generic combination. Lehtinen pointed out that this species is not very close to 
<taxonomicName id="36DA2DC9E235FFCD7010FE7A0793FE02" authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1981" box="[625,741,404,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Shearella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lilawati">
<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E235FFCD7010FE7A0793FE02" box="[625,741,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">S. lilawati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="36DA2DC9E235FFCD7142FE7A06DCFE02" authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1981" box="[803,938,404,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Shearella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="selvarani">
<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E235FFCD7142FE7A06DCFE02" box="[803,938,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">S. selvarani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He suggested to establish a new genus to accommodate this species, which, however, will be delayed until the discovery of females. Until then, it is better to include this species in 
<taxonomicName id="36DA2DC9E235FFCD73F5FE330758FE5A" authorityName="Gertsch" authorityYear="1941" box="[404,558,476,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Monoblemma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E235FFCD73F5FE330758FE5A" box="[404,558,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Monoblemma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than in 
<taxonomicName id="36DA2DC9E235FFCD70B3FE33064AFE5A" authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1981" box="[722,828,476,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Shearella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E235FFCD70B3FE33064AFE5A" box="[722,828,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Shearella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
